You type a number n — that’s how many steps you want in your staircase.

The code starts at step 1 and goes up to step n.

For each step:

It puts some spaces first so the step is pushed to the right (n - current step spaces).

Then it puts some # symbols for the step itself (current step number of #).

It prints the spaces and hashes together as one line.

Repeat until you reach the last step.

Boom — you get a staircase that looks right-aligned, like this if n = 6:
